SIMPLE: tubbing
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tubbing
<hw>Tub"bing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
forming of a tub; also, collectively, materials for tubs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A lining of timber or metal around the shaft of a
mine; especially, a series of cast-iron cylinders bolted together, used
to enable those who sink a shaft to penetrate quicksand, water, etc.,
with safety.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tubby</ent>⟦br⟧
